They aren't the cheapest, but they do offer in-and-out which is not the typically available unless you are staying in a place that has onsite valet.

Tips aren't included, but seriously, passing a guy $3-5 isn't going to hurt you.

originalText.text:
The garage is quite easy to find and decently priced compared to the surrounding garages. When I arrived, I shows my prepaid code and was told that tip was not included in the price.

I came back about an hour before my paid time. They had parked my car somewhere outside of the garage.

There was bird poop all over my car and I noticed that my antenna was in the passenger side of the car. When I asked the valet about it, he said they needed to take it off to avoid it being damaged. When I put it back on, I realized that it was bent and broken. When inquiring on how this was damaged, the valet told me I probably never noticed it before. I just purchased my car and know that the antenna was not damaged. He kept insisting it was my own fault and I did not realize that it was bent prior to dropping the car off.

I am unhappy with the attitude of the person that received my car and the person that did not take responsibility of the garage damaging my new car's antenna. I would not recommend.
